messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path: /users/{user}

- all HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: true
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:

- In routes/web.php you used Route::resource('users', UserController::class)->only('show'). The resource "show" action maps to the URI users/{user} and the controller method UserController::show, so the full path is /users/{user}.

- The resource registration creates a GET route for the "show" action (i.e. GET /users/{user}) and points it to UserController::show (which indeed exists and returns a view). Therefore GET is accepted.

- Laravel treats HEAD requests for a resource the same as GET (HEAD is implicitly supported for GET routes), so HEAD is accepted.

- No route registration in the provided files creates routes for POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, TRACE, or OPTIONS for this path, and there is no Route::any/Route::match covering all methods. Therefore those methods are not accepted based on the code shown.
